{{otheruses|Alcheringa (disambiguation)}}
'''Alcheringa Gallery''' is a [[contemporary art gallery]] in [[Victoria, British Columbia]], Canada that represents indigenous artists from Canada's [[British Columbia Coast|Northwest Coast]], [[Papua new guinea|Papua New Guinea]], [[Aboriginal Australia|Australia]], [[Solomon islands|Solomon Islands]], and [[Torres Strait]]. It was one of the first galleries to make use of the [[internet]] in 1996.<ref name="pion">{{Cite web|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=SL&p_theme=sl&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB04F7A87636A3F&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|title=Art Galleries Pioneer the 'Net|accessdate=2008-03-25|date=1996-01-15|author=Robert Steyer|work=St. Louis Post-Dispatch}}</ref>
